We can find the height of the cylinder using its volume. The formula for the volume of a cylinder is $\pi r^2 h$, where $r$ is the radius and $h$ is the height. We know that the volume of this cylinder is $45\pi$. So we have \begin{align*}
\pi r^2 h &= 45\pi \\
r^2 h &= 45\\
\frac{h}{r} &= \frac{45}{\pi}\\
h &= \boxed{\frac{45}{\pi}}
\end{align*} #### \frac{45}{\pi}

